The Governor of Lagos State, Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu, visited the Eti-Osa Driving Licence Centre of the Federal Road Safety Corps to renew his driving licence on Tuesday. In a statement on Tuesday by the Assistant Corps Marshal, Corps Public Education Officer, FRSC Headquarters, Abuja, Bisi Kazeem
said the governor was received by the Sector Commander, Lagos Sector Command, Corps Commander Olusegun Ogungbemide, in the company of some senior officers of the Corps who took the governor through the tripartite processes necessary for the biometric capture. The statement read, “The Lagos State governor visited our Eti-Osa centre to renew his driving licence. Reacting to the ease and smoothness of the entire process, Governor Sanwo-Olu was quoted, as saying it was “Very impressive, the entire staff was courteous. They all displayed a high level of professionalism. Keep it up. Many thanks” At the end of the biometrics, the governor was issued a temporary driving licence to be used pending when the permanent card would be ready. Earlier in the day, the First Lady, Dr. Ibijoke Sanwo-Olu also came for her physical capture and was handed her temporary driving licence by the Unit Commander Lagos Island, Esther Uzoma, and Sector Head, DLC CRC Oluwafemi Ige. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com